<abstract>
<t>This document describes WHOIS++, an extension to the trivial WHOIS service described in RFC 954 to permit WHOIS-like servers to make available more structured information to the Internet.  We describe an extension to the simple WHOIS data model and query protocol and a companion extensible, distributed indexing service.  A number of options have also been added such as the use of multiple languages and character sets, more advanced search expressions, structured data and a number of other useful features.  An optional authentication mechanism for protecting all or part of the associated WHOIS++ information database from unauthorized access is also described.</t></abstract></front>

